title: Dj.Nece's Classics of House mix
description:
What's hood people well I will help you define that with these old school house jams that still give a kick in some speakers and turn tables. This is my classics of house mix I dedicate to all my friends world wide that appreciate good classics and most of all to all those New York club heads. I did not take too much time for details but I did manage to pick some fun ones, these were some great times and I loaded this one for the 4th of July 2008 for the early birds in New York. Here is the track listing:

1.Masters At Work-Deep Inside
2.Todd Terry-Weekend
3.Masters At Work Feat. La India-I Can't Get No Sleep
4.Frankie Knuckles-The Whistle Song
5.Robert Owens-I'll Be Your Friend
6.Lil Louie Vega-French Kiss
7.Maurice-This Is Acid
8.Todd Terry-Bango
9.Two Without Hats-Esa Loca(dj.nece cut)
10.Jungle Brothers-I'll House You
11.Royal House-Can You Party(Todd Terry Mix)
12.Two Without Hats-The Breeze
13.Todd Terry-Babarabatiri(Masters At Work Main mix)
14.Two Without Hats-Boricua Posse

Music like this is not given the props it should be but I and all New Yorkers still rock this am sure. Keep it pumping, keep it loud, and most of all keep it alive. Great job all you artist, Producers, and most of all the Djs that made those floors stomp. For feed back you can catch me at my:
